<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd16512f6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s2354"><num value="2354">§ 2354.</num><heading> Termination</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">After <date date="1999-09-30">September 30, 1999</date>, the President—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idd16512f7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s2354/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> is not required to maintain a National Coordinator for Nonproliferation Matters under <ref href="/us/usc/t50/s2351">section 2351 of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idd16512f8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s2354/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> may terminate the Committee on Nonproliferation established under <ref href="/us/usc/t50/s2352">section 2352 of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idd16512f9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/201/dA/tXIV/s1444">Pub. L. 104–201, div. A, title XIV, § 1444</ref>, <date date="1996-09-23">Sept. 23, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/2730">110 Stat. 2730</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/105/261/dA/tX/s1069/c/3">Pub. L. 105–261, div. A, title X, § 1069(c)(3)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-17">Oct. 17, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/2136">112 Stat. 2136</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd16512fa-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd16512fb-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idd16512fc-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1998—<ref href="/us/pl/105/261">Pub. L. 105–261</ref> made technical amendments to references in original act which appear in par. (1) as reference to <ref href="/us/usc/t50/s2351">section 2351 of this title</ref> and in par. (2) as reference to <ref href="/us/usc/t50/s2352">section 2352 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
